# Sentinel Shield — Trivy filesystem-scan suppressions.
#
# The Sentinel Shield ENGINE ships no PHP production dependencies; its supply chain is the
# shell scripts, workflows, and schemas in this repo. The only composer.lock in the tree is a
# static TEST FIXTURE (tests/fixtures/projects/symfony/) that models a consumer project for
# install/detection tests — it is never `composer install`ed and is not part of the engine's
# supply chain. A fixture's pinned lock will perpetually accrue new advisories as the Trivy DB
# updates, so these fixture-only findings are suppressed here (with justification) to keep the
# engine fs scan meaningful for the engine's OWN dependencies.
#
# CEILING: the plain .trivyignore format cannot scope suppressions to a path, so these IDs
# are suppressed REPO-WIDE. Acceptable only because the engine has no production
# dependency manifests; if the engine ever gains a composer.lock/package-lock.json of its
# own, migrate to a path-scoped .trivyignore.yaml (and update the ci-docker.yml
# `trivyignores:` input) before adding any engine dependencies.
#
# symfony/yaml v7.0.0 (tests/fixtures/projects/symfony/composer.lock), new 2026 advisories:
CVE-2026-45133
CVE-2026-45304
CVE-2026-45305
